rComments: I love this man! He is by far the cutest, most pious, most caring and most intelligent academic you will ever meet. He has such a vast wealth of knowledge and yet he is able to work with whatever level you are at, and hes extremely humble. He really bonds with his students and hes definitely a dad in all aspects. Im gonna miss him so much... :(
Great Professor, a really great teacher and mentor. If you want to get excited about justice and the world, Dr. Locklin will give your enthusiasm and room to debate!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Participation matters']

rComments: This course isnt easy. A lot to read, but the weekly quiz is basically open book, and if u want good grades, participate. Its a full year, im silent for the fist (didnt do reading), got a D, and active for the 2nd, got an A. Hes fair and square. Long time to prep essay and exam (YES) He will give u in advance. Easy 4.0 AS LONG AS U DO PREPARATION.

Great class for a first year student, lecture were good, the tutorial readings were dry.  however Prof. Locklin was very good instructor.  He was accommodating when I needed assistance on more than one occasion.  The course really opened up my eyes about the church and its history plus, it will make any Catholic think.
Amazing Prof helped get me into my program!!

If you are Liberal,Humanist, anti-magesterial, Feminist, and hold any position which counters Roman Catholic Magesterial teaching this is the class for you. Dont offer any opinions, arguments, and papers which contradict the views expressed by your professorial host. Success in this environment comes by repeating verbatim the opinions of your host.
The most helpful, genuine prof you'll ever find.  Not what you'd expect for the "St. George" experience, because he actually CARES about all his students.  Also very knowledgeable.

THIS PROF IS AWESOME AS CAN BE! Although, I found the course boring at times [I took it last year], he made it fun. The jokes he tells are only funny when he tells it-noone can do what he does. simply amazing! and his fiance came to this lecture once! awwwwwwwwwwwwwww

Very passionate and enthusiastic.  I had him in his first year and you could see he was very into what he taught.  He was always willing to help us and go further into what was brought up or asked.  Receiving emails from him after class about what was talked about was always cool!

By the way, I prefer to say he's "handsome" not "hot"--I only use hot to describe my food. He's a very kind professor who makes class very interesting and he teaches from the heart. When you see him, you know he is a devout Catholic who loves God very much; Is it any wonder that he loves his students?? Take SMC103 with him! or any course with him.

Prof. Locklin is awesome!  I've never seen a prof with more dedication to his students.  He'd go to the ends of the earth to help you out!  He really knows his stuff, and his lectures are very imaginative.  His assignments allow for creative freedom and all examinations are fair.  He rocks!
Professor Locklin is the best prof at U of T.  He's incredibly passionate about his teaching, and very intelligent.  His class was really enjoyable.
There is no better teacher out there... seriously. Locklin is passionate & interested in the subject matter & cares about his students.  He rocks.

A great course - I strongly recommend it for those seeking to learn more about Catholicism as well as for those who wish to explore their personal spiritual journey. The course could not have had a better instructor.
greatest class and professor of all time.
